Each descriptor consists of a feature extraction mechanism, a description (in binary and XML format) and guidelines that define how to apply the descriptor on different kinds of media (e.g.
For retrieval applications, a rule for each descriptor is mandatory that defines how to measure the similarity of two descriptions.
The hypothesis is that analytically derived distance measures may be good in general but only a quantitative analysis is capable to identify the best distance measure for a specific feature extraction method.
The MPEG-7 standard defines - among others - a set of descriptors for visual media.
